This paper deals with the task of conducting visually grounded dialog, which involves learning goal-oriented cooperative dialog between autonomous agents who exchange information about a scene through several rounds of questions and answers in natural language. This task involves several sub-fields of computer science, including natural language processing (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and software engineering (cs.SD). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, and cs.SD, in that order.
